Effects of deworming on the prevalence of acute malnutrition and underweight cases among children below 5 years in Kenyan Counties from June 2021 to June 2023

Winnie Minayo Aditome

7/20/2023

Introduction

Undernutrition is a major challenge experienced by many African countries especially among children. According to a report by UNICEF 11% of children in Kenya are underweight and 4% suffer from acute malnutrition.This is attributed to food insecurity and insufficient care practices among others. One of the care practices includes health care practices such as deworming and vacinations.This analysis seeks to understand the effects of deworming efforts to the prevalence of acute malnutrition and underweight cases in Kenyan counties from January 2021 to June 2023.

Some of the questions the study seeks to answer are: 1.What is the correlation between deworming practices, acute malnutrition and underweight cases? 2.Are children who are underweight suffering from acute malnutrition?

Data Wrangling

The data used in this analysis was obtained from CEMA- UON. It can be accessed here https://github.com/cema-uonbi/internship_task/. The dataset contained the below variables: 1.Period (months from January 2021 to June 2023) 2.County (the 47 counties in Kenya) 3.Total number of children dewormed (Total Dewormed) 4.Number of children <5 years with acute malnutrition (Acute Malnutrition) 5.Number of children stunted (0-6 months, 6-23 months, 24-59 months) 6.Number of children <5 years with diarrhe (Diarrhea cases) 7.Number of children who are underweight (0-6 months, 6-23 months, 24-59 months)

## Analysis

  1. What is the correlation between deworming practices, acute malnutrition and underweight cases?
corr<- cor(Nutrition_3$Acute.Malnutrition,Nutrition_3$Total.Dewormed, method = 'pearson')
corr
## [1] NaN
corr2<- cor(Nutrition_3$Underweight,Nutrition_3$Total.Dewormed, method = 'pearson')
corr2

ggplot(Nutrition_3, aes(y=Total.Dewormed, x=Acute.Malnutrition))+
  geom_point()+
  labs(x="Acute Malnutrition", y="Total Dewormed")

ggplot(Nutrition_3, aes(y=Total.Dewormed, x=Underweight))+
  geom_point()+
  labs(x="Underweight", y="Total Dewormed")

2.Are children who are underweight suffering from acute malnutrition?

ggplot(Nutrition_3, aes(y=Underweight, x=Acute.Malnutrition))+
  geom_point()+
  labs(x="Acute Malnutrition", y="Underweight")

Conclusion

There was little correlation found between the deworming children and the prevalence of acute malnutrition and Undernutrition cases. More variables can be investigated to find out which factors are more correlated with the undernutrition rates in Kenya.
